					<description><![CDATA[<p>Crystalys Therapeutics raises $130 million in an oversubscribed Series B financing round. The funding will help Crystalys take its late-stage gout drug to market. Series B comes less than a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/crystalys-therapeutics-raises-130-million-gout-drug/" data-wpel-link="internal">Crystalys Therapeutics Raises $130 Million To Bring Late-Stage Gout Drug To U.S. Market</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Crystalys Therapeutics raises $130 million in an oversubscribed </span><a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/crystalys-therapeutics-announces-130-million-series-b-financing-to-advance-global-phase-3-development-and-commercialization-of-dotinurad-for-gout-302826763.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series B financing round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The funding will help Crystalys take its late-stage gout drug to market. Series B comes less than a year after its impressive $205 million Series A offering. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A large group of new and existing global biotech investors joined Frazier Life Sciences, the lead investor in the latest financing round. This new investment will give Crystalys a long financial runway. It fully supports the company’s continued worldwide late-stage clinical studies and provides the foundations for marketing the product in the United States and Europe.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Advancing Dotinurad Through Late-Stage Clinical Trials</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203713" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203713" class="size-large wp-image-203713" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Crystalys_Therapeutics_Logo-1024x536.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="536" /><p id="caption-attachment-203713" class="wp-caption-text">Crystalys Therapeutics Logo</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Crystalys will use the funding to advance ongoing global dotinurad development. Dotinurad is a once-daily oral URAT1 inhibitor. The therapy works by assisting the kidneys in excreting excess uric acid. It prevents painful gout flares and joint-damaging crystal buildups. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is currently advancing two pivotal Phase 3 registration studies, RUBY and TOPAZ. The RUBY trial compares dotinurad directly against allopurinol, the current standard first-line medication, in adults living with hyperuricemia.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, the TOPAZ study tests its therapeutic effectiveness in patients suffering from severe tophaceous gout. Additionally, proceeds will support the Phase 2 AMETHYST trial for patients intolerant to existing therapies.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/candid-health-raises-120m-ai-revenue-cycle-management/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Candid Health Raises $120M for AI Healthcare Revenue Platform</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A De-Risked Asset with Proven Real-World Efficacy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of the key strengths that dotinurad has for venture investors is the fact that it is so de-risked clinically. The compound was developed by the Japanese firm Fuji Yakuhin. It has been approved and is used in Japan, China, Taiwan, the Philippines and Thailand. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In 2024, Crystalys obtained commercial rights on a worldwide basis (excluding Asia). The U.S. Food and Drug Administration granted Crystalys Waiver of Early Clinical Phases. This is because there is extensive data available on the safety of the product in Asian markets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Directly advancing to late-stage Phase 3 trials reduced the typical drug development path by years and reduced the overall clinical risks faced by the company. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer James Mackay said the new capital will allow a longer running period for the company to operate beyond its expected Phase 3 clinical data readouts in 2027. Underpinned by strong financial support, Crystalys is making rapid strides towards commercial readiness and strategically assessing opportunities for the public market.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/humanoid-raises-152m-series-a-uk-robotics-unicorn/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Humanoid Raises $152 Million in Series A</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Closing a Critical Gap in Second-Line Gout Care</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gout is the most prevalent inflammatory arthritis. However, there are few therapeutic choices for millions of patients. About 50% of those who use the standard first-line treatments of uric acid. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Second-line options remain equally problematic for clinicians. Patients frequently face hard choices between costly biweekly intravenous infusions carrying severe infusion risks or alternative oral medications linked with cardiac warnings. Dotinurad directly targets this critical gap in second-line care. Its highly selective mechanism delivers strong urate-lowering power without causing kidney toxicity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The speedy close reflects a rise in investor interest in late-stage, high conviction biopharma assets. Founding investors such as Novo Holdings, SR One and Catalys Pacific were joined by prominent new crossover backers such as Wellington Management, HBM Healthcare Investments, Soleus Capital, and Cormorant Asset Management. </span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/microsoft-funds-mistrals-european-ai-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Microsoft To Fund Mistral’s European AI Expansion</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/crystalys-therapeutics-raises-130-million-gout-drug/" data-wpel-link="internal">Crystalys Therapeutics Raises $130 Million To Bring Late-Stage Gout Drug To U.S. Market</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
