					<description><![CDATA[<p>Arrakis Raises Funding To Accelerate Industrial AI Adoption London-based AI deployment company Arrakis announced it has raised roughly $38 million to scale its platform, which helps industrial companies inject AI</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/arrakis-raises-38m-to-scale-ai-deployment-for-industrial-operations/" data-wpel-link="internal">Arrakis Raises $38M to Scale AI Deployment for Industrial Operations</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Arrakis Raises Funding To Accelerate Industrial AI Adoption</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">London-based AI deployment company Arrakis announced it has raised roughly $38 million to scale its platform, which helps industrial companies inject AI agents into the critical workflows of their operations. The financing round includes a $30 million Series A from Blossom Capital and comes just 10 months after Arrakis raised $7.5 million in a seed round backed by Accel. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series A round was led by blossom Capital, with support from Accel as well as other participants including GFC, MainObject, Rerail, Datadog founder Olivier Pomel, Olivier Godement, head of business products at OpenAI, and Cambridge Aerospace founder Junaid Hussein. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funds will be used to triple Arrakis’ team size and bolster its security measures and the capacity of its AI platform, and to fuel its expansion in the European Union, the U.S., and the Middle East.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Agents Target Complex Industrial Workflows</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The AI startup, founded in January 2026 by Accel alum Rafael Quintanilla alongside co-founders Haroun Beltaifa, Romain Fouilland and Mikhail Galkov, is aimed at applying AI to industries where complexity and legacy infrastructure typically drag down digitalization. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The product works in industries like aerospace, manufacturing, logistics, energy, telco, and construction. Instead of substituting existing enterprise software, Arrakis injects AI agents directly into existing operational systems. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Combining AI engineers with an </span><a href="https://www.inbenta.com/articles/model-agnostic-ai-architecture" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">AI-model-agnostic</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> platform Arrakis allows organizations to train and manage their own custom AI agents with their data. The company gives companies control over their data and intellectual property and the platform supports multiple models as tech changes. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industrial companies are one of the largest opportunities for AI, given how much of the industry relies on siloed systems and manual processes. Our vision at Arrakis is to empower industrial organizations with the tools to digitize their operations while giving them absolute control over their performance, cost, and security, CEO Rafael Quintanilla said.</span></p>
<h2><b>Early Enterprise Customers Report Measurable Gains</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203703" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203703" class="size-full wp-image-203703" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Arrakis-2.png" alt="Illustration of an industrial AI platform automating procurement and operations, providing real-time business intelligence across global energy, logistics, and manufacturing enterprises." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203703" class="wp-caption-text">Early enterprise adoption of industrial AI is delivering measurable operational improvements, enabling faster procurement, real-time process visibility, and scalable automation across energy, logistics, and industrial organisations. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Within six months of its launch, Arrakis has secured enterprise customers across Europe and the United States, including several NYSE-listed companies operating in the energy, logistics, and industrial sectors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customers have already achieved measurable operational improvements. Some organisations have reduced procurement cycle times by as much as 90%, while others have gained real-time visibility into operational and financial processes that were previously managed manually.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Arrakis says its commercial model is closely tied to customer outcomes, with a significant portion of its fees linked directly to the value delivered. The company currently operates from offices in London and Paris and has already signed its first U.S. customer, reflecting growing international demand for industrial AI deployment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/glow-raises-180m-to-expand-ai-powered-endpoint-security-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Glow Raises $180M to Expand AI-Powered Endpoint Security Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Plans Focus On Global Industrial Markets</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fresh funding will help Arrakis strengthen its engineering and security capabilities while supporting rapid global expansion. The company plans to significantly increase headcount as it scales deployments across industrial markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As manufacturers, logistics providers, and energy companies continue modernising their operations, demand is expected to grow for AI platforms that can integrate with existing systems while maintaining strict security and data ownership requirements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With early customer traction and fresh capital, Arrakis aims to establish itself as a leading AI deployment platform for industrial organisations seeking to improve operational performance without replacing existing technology infrastructure.</span></p>
