]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">U.K. robotics startup Humanoid raises $152 million in </span><a href="https://x.com/TheHumanoidAI/status/2079557510315257980" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series A funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Humanoid now has a valuation of $1.35 billion, making it the U.K.’s very first AI robotics unicorn. Prime Movers Lab, a U.S. venture capital firm, led the funding round. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new round of funding brings Humanoid&#8217;s total funding to $270 million since its 2024 inception. The milestone marks Europe&#8217;s emergence as a major player in physical artificial intelligence and shows that European robotics companies can scale quickly to directly compete with their counterparts around the globe.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Building Physical AI for Industrial Work</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203688" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203688" class="size-full wp-image-203688" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Humanoid.jpg" alt="Side profile of Humanoid&apos;s white and black industrial robot mounted on an articulated leg and wheeled base platform." width="800" height="418" /><p id="caption-attachment-203688" class="wp-caption-text">HMND 01 Industrial Wheeled Robot. Image Credit: Humanoid</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Humanoid focuses on developing a range of purpose-built, wheel-driven robots, specifically designed for complex factory environments. The company says it&#8217;s emphasizing wheeled mobility with the development of a platform that provides better stability, speed and heavy payloads on industrial floors, unlike traditional bipedal humanoids that are dedicated to walking on two feet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The core of its technical ecosystem is KinetIQ, a proprietary physical artificial intelligence framework. Operating as the robot’s central brain, KinetIQ processes sensor data in real time to allow precise spatial reasoning. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This enables the machines to navigate busy work floors and perform intricate assembly tasks safely alongside human workers without heavy physical barriers. By tightly integrating proprietary hardware with native AI software, Humanoid addresses growing labor shortages across global manufacturing, logistics, and retail distribution centers.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/microsoft-funds-mistrals-european-ai-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Microsoft To Fund Mistral’s European AI Expansion</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Commercial Traction and Key Partnerships</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203689" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203689" class="size-large wp-image-203689" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Humanoid-raise-1024x576.jpeg" alt="Humanoid team posing in an industrial office under text announcing $152M raised at a $1.35B valuation with investor logos below." width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-203689" class="wp-caption-text">Series A Funding Announcement. Image Credit: Humanoid</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s billion-dollar valuation stems from swift commercial progress and high-profile industry partnerships. Humanoid has already formed strategic software and hardware alliances with major global technology leaders, including NVIDIA, SAP, Siemens, and Bosch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most impressively, the startup recently signed what stands as the industry’s largest publicly announced commercial agreement with motion technology giant Schaeffler. Under this multi-year partnership, </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Schaeffler will deploy thousands of Humanoid’s wheeled robots across its global manufacturing plants. Investors consider this massive deployment a clear signal that general-purpose industrial robotics is moving rapidly out of research laboratories and directly onto active production lines.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founder and Chief Executive Officer Artem Sokolov emphasized that transforming advanced physical AI into practical everyday industrial tools required intense execution speed from a dedicated engineering team. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By blending Europe’s rich industrial heritage with cutting-edge artificial intelligence, Humanoid enters its next development phase poised to redefine global industrial productivity for decades to come.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ant-international-raises-1-2-billion-for-global-scaling/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Ant International Raises $1.2B For Global Scaling</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Humanoid To Scale Production and Global Reach</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new capital will help Humanoid scale its operational infrastructure and expand research facilities to boost manufacturing. Humanoid currently employs more than 250 engineers and roboticists. It has offices in London, Boston, Vancouver and San Diego.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the new funding, Humanoid will push the commercial rollout of Beta-version robots to select enterprise customer facilities in Q4. Humanoid also plans to initiate full-scale mass production of its wheeled robots. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling manufacturing this early will help Humanoid establish strong market dominance in industrial automation. The startup will also look to enter general-purpose robotics. The funding is impressive because most physical AI investments have been concentrated in the United States and China. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Humanoid’s impressive trajectory proves that the U.K. and broader European startup ecosystems can build world-class, commercially viable robotics companies.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/natural-raises-30m-agentic-payments-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Natural Raises $30M to Build Payments Infrastructure for AI Agents</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/humanoid-raises-152m-series-a-uk-robotics-unicorn/" data-wpel-link="internal">Humanoid Raises $152 Million in Series A To Become the U.K.’s First AI Robotics Unicorn</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
